  "text": "In another yet to be properly published work [CITATION_1] , the authors apply a number of SR methods to the LR image, independently, to get various HR estimates which are then combined, on the basis of adaptive weights, to get the final result 8. The authors refer to their method as MSCN-n, where n is the number of employed inference modules. The reported results demonstrate superiority of MSCN to the state of the art methods -like A+, SCN and SRCNN -as far as image quality is concerned. The method is also shown to be efficient with a comparable performance to [CITATION_2] .",
